  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6772 sitting 5 points below the GEX flip at 6777, dealers are currently in buy-the-dip mode as they're long gamma and hedging delta-neutral. The massive positive gamma walls from 6775-6785 (all 24-27B+) create a strong magnet effect that should pull price back toward this zone, with dealers turning into sellers on any rally above 6777. The wall break and GEX surge events suggest recent volatility triggered dealer rehedging, but the PIN regime should reassert mean-reverting behavior quickly.\n\nKey levels: 6765 negative gamma floor where dealer buying accelerates, 6777 flip point, and the 6780-6785 zone where dealer selling pressure intensifies.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get pulled back up toward 6780 as dealers buy the current dip.",
